<!-- ===== PROGRAM 01: BAM ===== -->
<section class="program-bam" id="bam">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="program-layout">

      <div class="program-text">
        <div class="program-number">01</div>
        <div class="section-label">Advanced Materials</div>
        <h2 class="section-heading">AlMgB<sub style="font-size:0.65em">14</sub> Ceramic Coatings</h2>
        <p>The Performance Materials Lab holds two pending patent applications on AlMgB14, commonly known as <strong>BAM ceramic</strong>. This ultra-hard boride ceramic is being developed as a PFAS-free replacement for polytetrafluoroethylene (Teflon) in both cookware coatings and industrial surface applications.</p>
        <p>Our group has performed the <strong>first-ever optical characterization</strong> of BAM, building a formal lab research record (PML-OPT-2024-001). These measurements have revealed semiconducting behavior in the material, a finding that directly contradicts prior theoretical predictions of metallic character.</p>

        <div class="finding-block">
          <div class="finding-label">Key Discovery</div>
          <p>Optical characterization of BAM reveals semiconducting electronic structure. This result overturns prior theoretical consensus and opens new application pathways in functional coatings and optoelectronics.</p>
        </div>

        <p>A full NSF DMR/CER fundamental science proposal is in active development, targeting Physical Review Materials for publication of the optical and thermal characterization findings. This work also supports two patent applications: one for a PFAS-free cookware coating and one for a surface functionalization method.</p>

        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">NSF DMR/CER</span>
          <span class="tag">Patent Pending x2</span>
          <span class="tag">PFAS-Free</span>
          <span class="tag">Semiconductor</span>
          <span class="tag">Optical Characterization</span>
        </div>

        <div class="program-meta">
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-key">Target Outlet</span>
            <span class="meta-val">Physical Review Materials</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-key">Lab Record</span>
            <span class="meta-val">PML-OPT-2024-001</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-key">Applications</span>
            <span class="meta-val">Cookware coating, industrial surface functionalization</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-key">Funding Stage</span>
            <span class="meta-val"><strong>Proposal in development</strong></span>
          </div>
        </div>
